<issue
	id="NKS-2-RNTRILS"
   type="arm"
   linkend="Resource_management_arm.Resource_location"
   status="closed"
   category="major_technical"
   by="Nigel Shaw"
   date="2003-07-15"
 ballot_comment="yes" member_body="GB">
<description>
	This entity defines the fact that a means to hold resources.
	The Managed_resource entity describes the quantity at a location (implicitly at a moment in time). 
	Neither capture the fact that a resource may be found at the location, independent of time. This would be the natural target for a property such as "maximum stockholding", "minimum recommended stockholding", etc. As it is there is no logical home for such properties. 
</description>
<comment
   by="Leif Gyllstrom" 
   date="2003-10-13">
<description>Properties assigned to the Managed resource.
</description>
</comment>
</issue>

